From: Cline (audit B2) <audit@ask>
Date: Tue, 05 May 2026 10:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] cdx: gate /dev/cdx_ctrl ioctls on CAP_NET_ADMIN

Audit finding cdx-P0.04 (plans/audit/AUDIT-cdx.md).

Every CDX_CTRL_* ioctl writes hardware: FMan PCD classification rules,
mcast/QoS tables, conntrack offload entries, DPA params. Without a
capability check, any local user holding an open fd on /dev/cdx_ctrl
can reconfigure the entire fast-path.

/dev/cdx_ctrl is single-open and 0660 root:root by udev today, so the
common operational case already requires root. This patch is
defense-in-depth: hardens against (a) udev mis-config that could
broaden the device mode, (b) a process that has already inherited a
root-opened fd via setuid drop, and (c) future chrdev-permission bugs.

Both unlocked_ioctl and compat_ioctl paths are gated. EPERM is the
correct return per Documentation/security/credentials.rst — userspace
expects -1/EPERM, not -1/EINVAL, when a privileged operation is
denied.

Audit reference: plans/audit/AUDIT-cdx.md cdx-P0.04
Signed-off-by: Cline <audit@ask>
---
diff --git a/cdx/cdx_dev.c b/cdx/cdx_dev.c
--- a/cdx/cdx_dev.c
+++ b/cdx/cdx_dev.c
@@ -19,6 +19,7 @@
 #include <linux/uaccess.h>
 #include <linux/slab.h>
 #include <linux/fdtable.h>
+#include <linux/capability.h>
 
 #include "portdefs.h"
 #include "misc.h"
@@ -147,6 +148,16 @@ long cdx_ctrl_ioctl(struct file *filp, unsigned int cmd,
                 unsigned long args) 
 {
 int retval;
+
+/* B2/cdx-P0.04: every CDX_CTRL_* ioctl writes hardware (FMan PCD,
+ * mcast/QoS tables, conntrack offload entries). Without
+ * CAP_NET_ADMIN any local user holding an open fd on
+ * /dev/cdx_ctrl can reconfigure the fast-path. The chrdev is
+ * single-open and 0660 root:root by udev, so this is
+ * defense-in-depth against udev mis-config, fd-inherit-then-
+ * setuid-drop, and chrdev-permission bugs. */
+if (!capable(CAP_NET_ADMIN))
+return -EPERM;
 
 //DPA_INFO("%s::cmd %d\n", __FUNCTION__, cmd);
 switch (cmd) {
@@ -193,6 +204,9 @@ long cdx_ctrl_ioctl(struct file *filp, unsigned int cmd,
 long cdx_ctrl_compat_ioctl(struct file *filp, unsigned int cmd,
                 unsigned long args)
 {
+/* B2/cdx-P0.04: same gate as the native ioctl path. */
+if (!capable(CAP_NET_ADMIN))
+return -EPERM;
 DPA_INFO("%s::\n", __FUNCTION__);
 return 0;
 }